quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  88,19,"And at the mountains - how they are erected?"
  88,20,"And at the earth - how it is spread out?"
  88,21,"So remind, [O Muḥammad]; you are only a reminder."
  89,16,"But when He tries him and restricts his provision, he says, "
  89,17,"No!{1} But you do not honor the orphan",footnotes:1:It is not like you imagine. Rather, Allāh tries people through prosperity and hardship and rewards both gratitude and patience with honor in the Hereafter.
  89,18,"And you do not encourage one another to feed the poor."
  90,10,"And have shown him the two ways?{1}",footnotes:1:Of good and evil.
  90,11,"But he has not broken through the difficult pass.{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., the steep incline or obstacle. In other words, he has not spent in the cause of Allāh but only boasts of spending in front of others.
  90,12,"And what can make you know what is [breaking through] the difficult pass?"
  91,7,"And [by] the soul and He who proportioned it{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., balanced and refined it, creating in it sound tendencies and consciousness.
  91,8,"And inspired it [with discernment of] its wickedness and its righteousness,"
  91,9,"He has succeeded who purifies it,"
  92,4,"Indeed, your efforts are diverse."
  92,5,"As for he who gives and fears Allāh"
  92,6,"And believes in the best [reward],"
  93,1,"By the morning brightness"
  93,2,"And [by] the night when it covers with darkness,{1}",footnotes:1:And becomes still.
  93,3,"Your Lord has not taken leave of you, [O Muḥammad], nor has He detested [you]."